data.name: txtflr.Text
data.value: FLOOR TIMES - 1. Select at least four teachers, then select ‘NOT APPLICABLE’ on the next option if applicable 2. Click submit teachers, and you will be brought to floor times window, where you can see the floor times of all teachers in the current day. 3. Click reset if you want to make any changes in teachers, and repeat the process.

data.name: txtauth.Text
data.value: TEST AUTHORIZATIONS - 1. Click the Add New button to add a new test. Enter the accurate information in the PROPER FORMAT when prompted to. 2. Test and status will be displayed and updated each time it is a new day. 3. To remove, select the test by clicking on the list box, and clicking the remove button.

data.name: txttrack.Text
data.value: UNIT TRACKER - 1. Click on the Add Course button to add a new course by entering the course code. 2. A new control will now appear, with buttons for 17 units in that course. 3. Click on a unit button in a course when completed to highlight it green. Click on the button again to remove the highlighted ‘complete’ mark. 4. To remove a course, click on the remove course button and enter the course code accurately.

data.name: txttodo.Text
data.value: TO DO LIST - 1. Click on sticky notes to bring them into focus and to drag them around. When in focus, type in the sticky notes for functionality. 2. Double click on a sticky note to remove if not needed. Click on the add button to add a new sticky note. 3. Resize a sticky note by hovering along bottom or right edges of box, then the icon will direct you for the movements.
